SIMPLE: accipiter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Accipiter
<hw>Ac*cip"i*ter</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> E. <plw>Accipiters</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. L.
<plw>Accipitres</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., hawk.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of rapacious birds; one of
the Accipitres or Raptores.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>A bandage applied over the nose,
resembling the claw of a hawk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Accipitral</ent>⟦br⟧
